list.comment: DeliverPhone Class- Improved names of string

task.summary: Two new classes created. Person and Customer Class. Customer extends person class. Variables declared in Phone class. Getters and setters created. Variables declared in PhoneSpec Class. Getters and setters created.

DeliverPhone Class- Created a List Instanisated Phone Spec Class Courier Checks if phone has been recived and in their inventory by doing a search. Courier then checks name,address,serial number to check if the phone in the inventory.
Inventory class- Methods written clearly so anyone looking at code will understand whats going on. For example add phone Type migration List<Phone> Phone and Customer class instansiated. Address and name added with phone details to inventory. A List of Type Phone created for a search method. Inventory class returns a typesafe collection of matching phones
Enum Classes Memory,Network,Model created to introduce type safety.
Phone Class. getter and setters example of encapsulation. Phone class extends Customer. Example of inheritance. Made attributes final. Serial number should not be changed thus no setter.
PhoneSpec Class- Declared class variables-enum Created setters to allow search in PhoneDelivery class. boolean matches method created
Person class changed to Customer. Follows single responsibility principle.

PhoneSpec Class- Phone Spec is an example of aggregation from the Phone Class. Phone Spec abstracts the details about the phones specifications away from the phone class itself so that i can add new phone properties without affecting the phone class.
Inventory Class- Changed search mehtod to phoneSearch Phone class updated to inherit customer attributes. updated instanciation phoneSearch an example of polymorphisim. Treats all phones instances of phone. This makes my code flexible. If i were to break down my phone further and have example nokia phones or motorola phones it would still just do a search on either. I would not have to refractor or rewrite code. Liskov substitution principle is followed here. Instaniated phone properties do not alter anything in the inventory class.
enum classes- Example of encapulation. By encapsulating these variables I have made my code more robust ,flexible and easier to change. This means my code is loosley coupled. If my requirements changes I do not have to revamp all my code.
Customer Class. Made variables protected. They are now accessible in Phone class.
Phone Class- Phone now inherits customer properties name and address. These properties are used in the inventory class so the courier can match the right phone to the customer and address Class follows single responsibilty principle-they all do what they are supposed to do.
DeliverPhone Class- My if else statements to allow courier to search inventory violates DRY and SRP principle. This needs to be updated in next commit.
